{{Lunisolar November}} '''November 20''' is the 20th day of the month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its Rokuyō is {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, and the designated day is {{ill|Shakkō|ja|赤口|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Events == * In the 13th year of the Jian'an era ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[208]] – December 15): The Battle of Red Cliffs took place, where the allied forces of Sun Quan and Liu Bei defeated Cao Cao on the Yangtze River. * In the 1st year of the Kenryaku era ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1211]] – December 26): The monk {{ill|Hōnen|ja|法然|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}—who had been exiled to Tosa—was allowed to return to Kyoto’s eastern foothills (Higashiyama Otani). * In the 1st year of the Gen'nin era ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1224]] – December 31): The era name was changed from Shōgen to Gen'nin. * In the 4th year of the Meiji era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1871]] – December 31): Yamanashi Prefecture was established as the governing area covering the entirety of the former Kai Province.
== Births == * In the 2nd year of the Chōroku era ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1458]] – December 25): Ashikaga Tsuguhisa, a Sengoku-period warlord, was born (died 1541). * In the 4th year of the Enpō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1676]] – December 24): Hosokawa Nobunori, the 4th lord of the Kumamoto Domain, was born (died 1732). * In the 2nd year of the Tenmei era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1782]] – December 24): Mōri Tadayoshi, lord of the Chōshū Domain, was born (died 1809). * In the 5th year of the Ansei era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1858]] – December 24): Ozaki Yukio, a politician known as the "God of Constitutionalism," was born (died 1954). * In the 4th year of the Meiji era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1871]] – December 31): Fukai Eigo, a politician, was born (died 1945).
== Deaths == * In the 2nd year of Emperor Saimei’s reign ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[643]] – December 30): Prince Yamase Ōe, a member of the imperial family and son of Prince Shōtoku, died. * In the 4th year of Emperor Saimei’s reign ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[658]] – December 11): Prince Arima, a son of Emperor Tenmu, died. * In the 4th year of the Teiwa era / 3rd year of the Shōhei era ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1348]] – December 2): Emperor Hanazono, the 95th Emperor of Japan, died (born 1297).
