{{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=十一月二十|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 11월 20일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar November|qq=}} '''November 20''' is the 20th day of the month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/November (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its Rokuyō is {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}}, and the designated day is {{ill|Shakkō|ja|赤口|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shakkō|qq=}}.
== Events == * In the 13th year of the Jian'an era ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[208]] – December 15): The Battle of Red Cliffs took place, where the allied forces of Sun Quan and Liu Bei defeated Cao Cao on the Yangtze River. * In the 1st year of the Kenryaku era ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1211]] – December 26): The monk [[:en:Hōnen|Hōnen]]—who had been exiled to Tosa—was allowed to return to Kyoto’s eastern foothills (Higashiyama Otani). * In the 1st year of the Gen'nin era ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1224]] – December 31): The era name was changed from Shōgen to Gen'nin. * In the 4th year of the Meiji era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1871]] – December 31): Yamanashi Prefecture was established as the governing area covering the entirety of the former Kai Province.
== Births == * In the 2nd year of the Chōroku era ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1458]] – December 25): Ashikaga Tsuguhisa, a Sengoku-period warlord, was born (died 1541). * In the 4th year of the Enpō era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1676]] – December 24): Hosokawa Nobunori, the 4th lord of the Kumamoto Domain, was born (died 1732). * In the 2nd year of the Tenmei era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1782]] – December 24): Mōri Tadayoshi, lord of the Chōshū Domain, was born (died 1809). * In the 5th year of the Ansei era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1858]] – December 24): Ozaki Yukio, a politician known as the "God of Constitutionalism," was born (died 1954). * In the 4th year of the Meiji era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1871]] – December 31): Fukai Eigo, a politician, was born (died 1945).
== Deaths == * In the 2nd year of Emperor Saimei’s reign ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[643]] – December 30): Prince Yamase Ōe, a member of the imperial family and son of Prince Shōtoku, died. * In the 4th year of Emperor Saimei’s reign ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[658]] – December 11): Prince Arima, a son of Emperor Tenmu, died. * In the 4th year of the Teiwa era / 3rd year of the Shōhei era ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1348]] – December 2): Emperor Hanazono, the 95th Emperor of Japan, died (born 1297).
